  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package embeds W-AR-05 (comparator absence or mismatch) via D3 undercutting: the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link, while the comparator used in supporting results is drawn from a ventricular assist device (VAD) operating regime rather than the CPB regime declared in the COU — a mismatch that is obscured by the overlapping pump geometry and similar QoI nomenclature.",
